snippet.textDisplay: My only gripe with this game as of yet (aside from the crossbow) is that it's pacing is so slow. snippet.textDisplay: I felt that Neuromancer had a larger influence on the game, especially with the augmentations. Example: in Neuromancer people put little chips in their heads to get certain effects, like telling whether or not someone is being used like a mobile camera. In Deus Ex we have the Targeting aug that gives us information of people and things. Both can be activated at will. The only difference between the two is that augmentations are internal and the chips stick out of one's neck, behind the ear.
